The article is a speech given by President Biden at the Capitol Rotunda in Washington, D.C. He pays tribute to Capitol Police Officer William "Billy" Evans, who was killed in the line of duty. The President describes Billy as someone he can relate to, having grown up with similar individuals in Pennsylvania. He acknowledges the strain and responsibility placed on the shoulders of Capitol Police and praises their courage. President Biden addresses Billy's mother, expressing his condolences and sharing his own experience of losing family members. He offers words of comfort, saying that while the pain may never fully go away, there will come a time when memories will bring smiles instead of tears. He emphasizes the heroism of Billy and assures the family that he will always be a part of them. The President concludes by expressing his prayer for the family to find moments of happiness amidst the grief.